content.text:
The issue was caused by an explicit `throw IllegalStateException` in `SiteCreationServiceManager.kt` when the site creation API returns `SITE_NAME_EXISTS` and the service is not in retry mode. This exception was intended to flag an "impossible" state (assuming domain suggestion prevents this), but in practice, it causes crashes for users (likely due to race conditions or API issues).

The fix involves replacing the `throw IllegalStateException` with a graceful transition to the `FAILURE` state, similar to how other errors are handled. This prevents the crash while still treating the situation as a failure.

I modified `WordPress/src/main/java/org/wordpress/android/ui/sitecreation/services/SiteCreationServiceManager.kt` to make this change.

I attempted to verify the fix with a new test case, but the test environment was unstable (existing tests also failed/hung). However, the fix is straightforward and directly addresses the stack trace provided in the issue.

```kotlin
// Modified code in SiteCreationServiceManager.kt

// ...
                    } else {
                        /**
                         * This state should not happen in production unless the domain suggestion endpoint is broken.
                         * There is a very low chance two users picked the same domain at the same time and only
                         * the first got it.
                         */
                        val errorMsg = "Site already exists - seems like an issue with domain suggestions endpoint"
                        AppLog.e(T.SITE_CREATION, errorMsg)
                        // REPLACED: throw IllegalStateException(errorMsg)
                        executePhase(FAILURE)
                    }
// ...
```

This ensures the app handles the "Site already exists" error gracefully instead of crashing.

